# Citation metadata (https://citation-file-format.github.io/).
cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Spaghetti Architect or its dataset, please cite it as below."
title: "Spaghetti Architect: a by-construction-labelled, contamination-resistant, multi-language code dataset generator"
abstract: >-
  Spaghetti Architect maps a clean JSON intermediate representation to deliberately
  redundant, fully-flattened, yet provably-correct code in Python, JavaScript, Go,
  Java and C++, gated by an oracle validator. It mints code datasets with
  by-construction labels along two orthogonal difficulty axes -- intrinsic complexity
  (problem size) and incidental complexity (presentation mess at fixed semantics) --
  and resists contamination by minting fresh variants from a private held-out seed.
  The public dev split and the generator support contamination-controlled LLM
  evaluation, training/probing of code models, and robustness studies (refactoring,
  LLM-as-judge quality, and output-prediction comprehension tasks).
type: software
version: "0.2.0"
date-released: "2026-06-21"
license: "MIT"
repository-code: "https://github.com/KurathSec/Spaghetti-Architect"
